race.description: K Brereton Showcase Jewellers Mdn Plate
race.comment: Another maiden that looks pretty thin on paper. ME NAME'S BORIS (3) started a big price and finished midfield in a stronger maiden at Murray Bridge last start. This looks an easier assignment and he'll be improved for the race experience. Rochelle Milnes and a low draw are both in his favour. He can win. LITTLE ROCKET (2) comes out of the same race at Murray Bridge and was arguably more impressive than ME NAME'S BORIS, running on from near-last. He might end up three back on the fence so he will need luck but can run well. SPLASH OF WHITE (11) jumps sharply in trip and her best run was over this track and distance last campaign. She will need to improve but she can run in the money. BOOMA BAY (1) and BROADWAY DANCER (7) are both capable of running top three.
